videos.description: Ohio State QB J.T. Barrett gets picked off by Amani Hooker, who returns it 30 yards for the Iowa touchdown.
videos.headline: Barrett throws pick-six on first play

videos.description: J.T. Barrett makes up for his pick-six with a 29-yard touchdown pass to Terry McLaurin for the Buckeyes.
videos.headline: Barrett finds McLaurin wide open for Ohio State TD

videos.description: Akrum Wadley gets a big 30-yard gain up the sideline for the Hawkeyes.
videos.headline: Wadley goes 30 yards on his first run for Iowa

videos.description: J.K. Dobbins gets outside with a burst of speed and goes 35 yards into Iowa territory.
videos.headline: Dobbins gets a big 35-yard gain for Ohio State

videos.description: Iowa quarterback Nathan Stanley connects with T.J. Hockenson on a 10-yard touchdown to give them the lead over Ohio State.
videos.headline: Stanley throws first TD for Hawkeyes

videos.description: J.T. Barrett fires a 44-yard touchdown pass to Johnnie Dixon to tie it up for the Buckeyes.
videos.headline: Barrett connects with Dixon for huge Ohio State TD

videos.description: Ohio State's Nick Bosa is ejected for targeting after following through on a hit to Iowa quarterback Nathan Stanley's chin.
videos.headline: Bosa ejected for targeting

videos.description: Iowa quarterback Nathan Stanley connects with Noah Fant on a 25-yard touchdown immediately following the ejection of Nick Bosa to give the Hawkeyes the lead.
videos.headline: Stanley finds Fant in corner for TD

videos.description: J.T. Barrett is picked off by Iowa's Joshua Jackson late in the second quarter.
videos.headline: J.T. Barrett throws second pick of first half

videos.description: Nathan Stanley rolls out and finds Noah Fant open in the end zone for an easy 3-yard touchdown increasing the Hawkeye lead.
videos.headline: Fant gets open for another Iowa TD

videos.description: Ohio State head coach Urban Meyer says his team needs to make adjustments to deal with Iowa's aerial threat.
videos.headline: Meyer: 'Turnovers were costly'

videos.description: Iowa Akrum Wadley breaks multiple tackles and scrambles for 22 yards.
videos.headline: Wadley dodges defenders for big run

videos.description: Iowa quarterback Nathan Stanley manages to keep his feet as a defender tries to wrap him up on a 2-yard touchdown pass to T.J. Hockenson.
videos.headline: Iowa's Stanley delivers TD pass despite defender holding his leg

videos.description: James Butler cuts through the defense and goes 53 yards to get Iowa inside the Ohio State 5 yard line.
videos.headline: Butler breaks out for huge gain into red zone for Iowa

videos.description: Nathan Stanley throws his 5th touchdown of the game to Drake Kulick as Iowa score 28 unanswered points.
videos.headline: Stanley pours it on for Iowa with his 5th TD

videos.description: J.T. Barrett is picked off for the third time today by Iowa's Joshua Jackson deep inside Ohio State territory.
videos.headline: Barrett throws 3rd interception

videos.description: Joshua Jackson makes an incredible one-handed interception to pick off J.T. Barrett for the fourth time today.
videos.headline: Iowa's Jackson picks off Barrett for 4th time

videos.description: J.T. Barrett finds Johnnie Dixon for the second time today, this time for a 22-yard Buckeye touchdown.
videos.headline: Dixon makes 2nd TD catch for Buckeyes

videos.description: Iowa running back converts a 6-yard touchdown putting them over the 50 mark against Ohio State.
videos.headline: Toren Young pours it on for the Hawkeyes

videos.description: Iowa's Joshua Jackson talks about what it means to play at Kinnick Stadium and how they keep pulling off these upsets.
videos.headline: Jackson: 'The stadium gives us such a great vibe'

videos.description: Steve Levy and Brian Griese discuss Iowa's destruction of Ohio State at home and whether the Big Ten is out of contention for a playoff spot.
videos.headline: Iowa capitalizes on Barrett interceptions

videos.description: The No. 6 Buckeyes give up their most points since Oct. 29, 1994 in a 55-24 loss to the Hawkeyes.
videos.headline: Iowa's offense crushes Ohio State
